{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609856"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:52:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:52:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16129"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16129","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16129"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.72,0.07,0.03,0.14,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8820"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114305"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8820"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16129"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96305"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7030"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21040"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21043"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114305","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114305"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe external genitalia develop from several embryonic precursor structures. These structures differentiate under hormonal influence to form either male or female external genitalia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following embryonic structures gives rise to the clitoris?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Genital tubercle","Urogenital folds","Labioscrotal swellings","Urogenital sinus","Cloacal membrane"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egenital tubercle\u003C/strong\u003E is the embryonic precursor that develops into the clitoris in females and the penis in males. This sexual differentiation occurs in response to the presence or absence of androgens during embryonic development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUrogenital folds\u003C/strong\u003E develop into the labia minora in females and ventral aspect of the penis including the penile urethra in males. \u003Cstrong\u003ELabioscrotal swellings\u003C/strong\u003E form the labia majora in females and fuse to create the scrotum in males. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eurogenital sinus\u003C/strong\u003E contributes to the formation of the distal vagina, vestibule and urethra in females. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecloacal membrane\u003C/strong\u003E breaks down during development to form separate urogenital and anal openings. The bipotential nature of these precursor structures allows them to develop into either male or female structures depending on the hormonal environment during embryogenesis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The clitoris develops from the genital tubercle during embryonic development.","The genital tubercle is a common precursor structure that develops into either the clitoris in females or penis in males depending on hormonal signals.","Other genital precursor structures include the urogenital folds and labioscrotal swellings which form different parts of external genitalia."],"references":["Baskin L, Shen J, Sinclair A, Cao M, Liu X, Liu G, Isaacson D, Overland M, Li Y, Cunha GR. Development of the human penis and clitoris. Differentiation. 2018 Sep-Oct;103:74-85. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2018.08.001. Epub 2018 Aug 23. PMID: 30249413; PMCID: PMC6234061.","Cunha GR, Baskin LS. Development of the external genitalia. Differentiation. 2020 Mar-Apr;112:7-9. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2019.10.008. Epub 2019 Dec 4. PMID: 31881402; PMCID: PMC7138693","Nguyen JD, Duong H. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Female External Genitalia. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK547703/","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96305"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16129"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96305","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96305"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T14:52:40+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T14:52:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8820"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114305"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"t